**Flag reason:** The old XML doc comment on `AadClientId` said *"used for app auth or managed identity"* ŌĆö intentionally covering all auth modes. The new `ManagedIdentityClientId` doc comment says *"used for DefaultAzureCredential"* exclusively. This is functionally correct given that the multi-mode auth was stripped, but the old comments were guiding future readers that this client ID served multiple roles. The post-PR comment accurately reflects the narrowed scope, so this is well-handled. Ō£ģ No real issue here either.

